                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.199/66: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Jean de Luz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-08T19:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 8, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 8—3:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>409. Bay’s telegram of December 6, 11 a.m. Military Commandant at Irun received
                    Queipo de Llano’s telegram urging him to facilitate Chapman’s return to Bilbao
                    but regrets that Sangroniz’s orders make it impossible to grant the <hi
                        rend="italic">salvo conducto</hi>. He is calling the General’s telegram to
                    the attention of the diplomatic cabinet. Under the circumstances Chapman leaves
                    on the 15th and I shall do no more in the Bilbao matter for the present.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
